To use the programs in this folder, you first need to add it to the Python path in your environment with "export PYTHONPATH=~/path/to/topmon/contrib/baip/Python:$PYTHONPATH" (you can also add the line to your $HOME/.bashrc file so that it is loaded every time you log in).
------------------------------------------------------------
genrep.py is a program to extract various properties (e.g., vapor pressures, densities, enthalpies of vaporization; the behavior can be configured) from simulation output and to do proper averaging. It makes use of simutil.py and statistics.py.
------------------------------------------------------------
procall.py is a program to set up input files and optimize simulation parameters. It uses simutil.py. You need to modify the code according to the particular circumstances of your simulations. Be ultra cautious when you use this kind of script: go through the file and make sure you understand each and every line.
------------------------------------------------------------
exGaussian.py can be used in two ways:
(1) Extract energies from Gaussian scan output files (REMEMBER: Gaussian uses the protein convention for dihedral angles; i.e., trans is 180 deg):
$ /path/to/exGaussian.py --qmenergy -i gaussian.log -o qmenergy.txt [-x index.txt/--nbead N] -s scanList.txt

(2) Subtract energies from MM runs using topmon:
$ /path/to/exGaussian.py --mmenergy -i qmenergy.txt -o mmenergy.txt -e /path/to/topmon
------------------------------------------------------------
cfg2pdb.py and xyz2pdb.py are two small scripts to convert system configurations generated by topmon to the PDB format for visualization. Both uses convert2pdb.py.
(1) cfg2pdb.py converts config1a.dat, fort.77, etc.:
$ /path/to/cfg2pdb.py /path/to/cfg

(2) xyz2pdb.py converts boxIconfig1a.xyz, etc.:
$ /path/to/xyz2pdb.py /path/to/xyz /path/to/output_pdb
